msgid ""
"**Step for the hours (minutes)** Amount of minutes between each step for "
"minutes under an hour in duration dropdowns. Example: 5 minutes shows 5, "
"10, 15, 20, ..., 55, 60."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/general/assistance.rst:18
msgid ""
"**Default file size limit imported by the mails receiver** Maximum size "
"of files to allow to import by the mail collector. This should be "
"adjusted along with the maximum file size option on the `management tab "
"<management.html>`_ and the `max_upload_size` PHP directive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/general/assistance.rst:22
msgid ""
"**Default heading when adding a document to a ticket** Allows you to set "
"a default classification for documents uploaded to a ticket."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/general/assistance.rst:25
msgid ""
"**Keep tickets when purging hardware in the inventory** If enabled, the "
"tickets related to an asset being purged will remain. Otherwise, they are"
" purged along with the asset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/general/assistance.rst:29
msgid ""
"**Allow anonymous ticket creation (helpdesk.receiver)** Anonymous ticket "
"creation is disabled by default. Activating the option is necessary when "
"using a collector or the anonymous ticket entry form to allow the "
"creation of tickets by users not recognized by GLPI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/general/assistance.rst:33
msgid ""
"**Limit of the schedules for planning** Time range displayed in the "
"planning screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/general/assistance.rst:36
msgid ""
"**By default, a software may be linked to a ticket** Allow associating a "
"software with a ticket by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/general/assistance.rst:39
msgid ""
"**Show personal information in new ticket form (simplified information)**"
" Display the name, phone number, and location of the user. If needed, the"
" **Edit** button redirects to the main tab of the user's preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/general/assistance.rst:43
msgid ""
"**Allow anonymous followups (receiver)** Allows a user not present in "
"GLPI to respond to an email from GLPI."
msgstr ""

